('The Lord of the Rings', 'J. R. R. Tolkien', 99, '9780261103207', 'Allen & Unwin', '1954-07-29', 'An epic high fantasy novel by J. R. R. Tolkien. The story began as a sequel to Tolkien’s 1937 children’s book The Hobbit, but eventually developed into a much larger work set in Middle-earth1.',10, TRUE),
('Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince', 'J. K. Rowling', 55, '9780439784542', 'Bloomsbury Publishing (UK)', '2005-07-16', 'A fantasy novel written by British author J. K. Rowling. It is the sixth and penultimate novel in the Harry Potter series. The novel explores the past of the boy wizard’s nemesis, Lord Voldemort, and Harry’s preparations for the final battle against Voldemort.',10, TRUE),
('The Da Vinci Code', 'Dan Brown', 251, '0385504209', 'Doubleday', '2003-04-02', 'A mystery thriller novel by Dan Brown. The novel explores the secret history of the holy grail and the conflict between religion and science.',10, TRUE),
('Fifty Shades of Grey', 'E. L. James', 27, '9781612130286', 'Vintage Books', '2012-04-17', 'An erotic romance novel by E. L. James. The story follows the relationship between a college graduate, Anastasia Steele, and a young business magnate, Christian Grey.',10, TRUE),
('Twilight', 'Stephenie Meyer', 38, '0316160172', 'Little, Brown and Company', '2005-10-05', 'A vampire-themed fantasy romance novel by Stephenie Meyer. The story revolves around Bella Swan, a girl who moves to Forks, Washington, and falls in love with a 104-year-old vampire named Edward Cullen.',10, TRUE),
('Hannibal', 'Thomas Harris', 67, '0385334877', 'Delacorte Press', '1999-06-08', 'A psychological horror novel by Thomas Harris. The novel is the third entry in Harris’s Hannibal Lecter series, following Red Dragon and The Silence of the Lambs.',10, TRUE),
('The Hunger Games', 'Suzanne Collins', 132, '9780439023528', 'Scholastic Press', '2008-09-14', 'A dystopian novel by Suzanne Collins. The story is set in the ruins of a place once known as North America, now known as Panem. A cruel government, located in the Capitol, requires each of its twelve outlying districts to send a teenage boy and girl to participate in the annual Hunger Games',0, FALSE),
('Life of Pi', 'Yann Martel', 27, '0676973760', 'Knopf Canada', '2001-09-11', 'A philosophical novel by Yann Martel. The story follows a young Indian boy named Pi, who finds himself shipwrecked and lost at sea in a large lifeboat with four wild animals.',10, TRUE),
('The Last Olympian', 'Rick Riordan', 151, '9781423101475', 'Disney Hyperion', '2009-05-05', 'A fantasy-adventure novel by Rick Riordan. It is the fifth and final book in the Percy Jackson & the Olympians series. The story revolves around the demigod Percy Jackson as he leads his friends in a last stand to protect Mount Olympus',0, FALSE),
('1984', 'George Orwell', 20, '0451524934', 'Signet Classics', '1949-06-08', 'A dystopian social science fiction novel by George Orwell. The story is set in Airstrip One, a province of the superstate Oceania in a world of perpetual war, omnipresent government surveillance, and public manipulation',0, FALSE),
('To Kill a Mockingbird', 'Harper Lee', 18, '9780060935467', 'Harper Perennial Modern Classics', '1960-07-11', 'A novel by Harper Lee. The story is renowned for its warmth and humor, despite dealing with serious issues of rape and racial inequality.',10, TRUE),
('The Great Gatsby', 'F. Scott Fitzgerald', 15, '0743273567', 'Scribner', '1925-04-10', 'A novel by F. Scott Fitzgerald. The story primarily concerns the young and mysterious millionaire Jay Gatsby and his quixotic passion and obsession with the beautiful former debutante Daisy Buchanan.',10, TRUE),
('Pride and Prejudice', 'Jane Austen', 20, '193659451X', 'Penguin Books', '1813-01-28', 'A romantic novel of manners written by Jane Austen. The novel follows the character development of Elizabeth Bennet, the dynamic protagonist of the book who learns about the repercussions of hasty judgments and comes to appreciate the difference between superficial goodness and actual goodness.',10, TRUE),
('Catch-22', 'Joseph Heller', 22, '1451626657', 'Simon & Schuster', '1961-11-10', 'A satirical war novel by Joseph Heller. The novel is set during World War II, from 1942 to 1944. It mainly follows the life of Captain John Yossarian, a U.S. Army Air Forces B-25 bombardier.',10, TRUE),
('The Catcher in the Rye', 'J.D. Salinger', 20, '0316769487', 'Little, Brown and Company', '1951-07-16', 'A novel by J.D. Salinger. The novel’s protagonist Holden Caulfield has become an icon for teenage rebellion. The novel also deals with complex issues of innocence, identity, belonging, loss, and connection.',10, TRUE);
